Swaziland Needs Supplementary Budget as Fiscal Crisis Deepens, IMF Says

-- B y   G o r d o n   B e l l
-- 
2011-08-31T14:45:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/swaziland-needs-supplementary-budget-as-fiscal-crisis-deepens-imf-says.html
Swaziland’s fiscal crisis is
worsening and the country will continue to face severe liquidity
constraints in coming months even after  South Africa  agreed to
an emergency loan, the  International Monetary Fund  said.  Swaziland’s governent should approve a supplementary budget
that cuts the state wage bill and  capital spending , the
Washington-based institution said in a statement on its website
today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Gordon Bell  at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  